    "source": "IFRS_9",
    "type": "appendix",
    "title": "Measurement (Chapter 5)",
    "subtitle": "Gains and losses (Section 5.7)",
    "subsection": "Liabilities designated as at fair value through profit or loss",
    "subsubsection": "Determining the effects of changes in credit risk",
    "qdrant_id": "d2e7c67a-da8d-56b0-9e0f-a63bd3e73579",
    "chunk_id": 1,
    "content": "IFRS_9 | Determining the effects of changes in credit risk | B5.7.17 Changes in market conditions that give rise to market risk include changes in a benchmark interest rate, the price of another entity’s financial instrument, a commodity price, a foreign exchange rate or an index of prices or rates.\n\nB5.7.18 If the only significant relevant changes in market conditions for a liability are changes in an observed (benchmark) interest rate, the amount in paragraph B5.7.16(a) can be estimated as follows: (a) First, the entity computes the liability’s internal rate of return at the start of the period using the fair value of the liability and the liability’s contractual cash flows at the start of the period. It deducts from this rate of return the observed (benchmark) interest rate at the start of the period, to arrive at an instrument-specific component of the internal rate of return. (b) Next, the entity calculates the present value of the cash flows associated with the liability using the liability’s contractual cash flows at the end of the period and a discount rate equal to the sum of (i) the observed (benchmark) interest rate at the end of the period and (ii) the instrument-specific component of the internal rate of return as determined in (a). (c) The difference between the fair value of the liability at the end of the period and the amount determined in (b) is the change in fair value that is not attributable to changes in the observed (benchmark) interest rate. This is the amount to be presented in other comprehensive income in accordance with paragraph 5.7.7(a)."
